# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share this in the git repo
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used in a library, you may want to ignore Pipfile.lock.
#   In case of a tool/app, you should definitely commit Pipfile.lock.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally committed, but you can ignore it if needed.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally committed, but you can ignore it if needed.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; project local packages directory (used by pdm)
